---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import NextReleaseBadge from '../../components/NextReleaseBadge.astro';

const shapes = [
  {
    title: '1. Embedded in a Rust service (single-process)',
    body: `The original use case. <code>tflo-core</code> runs inline in the user's service;
      records flow through <code>Iterator::tflo(...)</code> or
      <code>Stream::tflo(...)</code>; no external runtime is involved. Keyed execution still
      works single-process via <code>LocalShard</code> &mdash; the default
      <code>ShardRouter</code> impl in <code>tflo_core::shard</code>.`,
    try: `Every example under <code>tflo-examples/examples/</code> <em>except</em>
      <code>iot-portal</code> runs in this mode.`,
    caveats: 'None specific to this shape.',
    badge: null,
  },
  {
    title: '2. Edge gateway (Linux / ARM, tokio + std)',
    body: `A single-process Rust binary on a sensor gateway. Consume sensor input (MQTT,
      OPC-UA, Modbus, vendor protocol), condition it (SMA, hysteresis, debounce), and
      republish lifecycle events upstream (Kafka, NATS, or a TSDB sink). Engine:
      <code>tflo-core</code>. Source: <code>tflo-connect-mqtt</code> with the pure-Rust
      <code>rumqttc-backend</code> feature &mdash; cross-compiles cleanly to
      <code>armv7-unknown-linux-gnueabihf</code>. State:
      <code>tflo-state-files</code> with the <code>async</code> feature for crash-safe
      restart. Sink: typically MQTT producer or <code>tflo-sink-influx</code>.`,
    try: `The <em>edge gateway</em> leg of <code>tflo-examples/examples/iot-portal/</code>.`,
    caveats: `MQTT QoS-2 dedup needs a bounded window; <code>MqttCursor</code> enforces this
      so the in-flight set cannot grow unbounded.`,
    badge: 'next',
  },
  {
    title: '3. Central worker cluster (Kafka-sharded)',
    body: `Multiple worker processes each owning a slice of the keyspace, driven by Kafka
      consumer-group rebalancing. State per partition is durable in an
      <code>AsyncStateStore</code> (S3, Postgres, file, &hellip;) so a worker that loses a
      partition during rebalance can have it restored elsewhere. Engine:
      <code>tflo-core</code> async. Source: <code>tflo-connect-kafka</code> with
      <code>rdkafka-backend</code> for production. Shard router:
      <code>KafkaShardRouter</code> &mdash; the <code>AsyncStateStore</code> argument is
      <strong class="text-white">required</strong> at construction (a compile-time poka-yoke
      against running sharded execution with no durable state). State:
      <code>tflo-state-files</code> for dev, <code>tflo-state-s3</code> for production.
      Sink: <code>tflo-sink-influx</code>, <code>tflo-arrow</code> for Parquet archive, or
      back-to-Kafka. Orchestration: <code>Checkpointer</code> &mdash; writes snapshot first,
      cursor last (crash-safe order), per-stage deadline, consecutive-failure circuit
      breaker.`,
    try: `The <em>central worker</em> leg of <code>tflo-examples/examples/iot-portal/</code>.`,
    caveats: `At-least-once delivery; sinks should be idempotent (use
      <code>Deduplicator</code>). The router's <code>AssignmentEpoch</code> must be re-read
      on every event intake for the rebalance-race fence to work.`,
    badge: 'next',
  },
  {
    title: '4. WASM (browser / edge runtime)',
    body: `<code>tflo-core</code> and <code>tflo-ops</code> build clean for
      <code>wasm32-unknown-unknown</code>; <code>tflo-wasm</code> exposes the streaming
      detectors to JS. For larger graphs in this shape, mind the wasm32 4 GiB per-instance
      memory cap &mdash; per-key state grows with key cardinality. Set
      <code>KeyedConfig::max_active_keys</code> (LRU eviction to a snapshot store) when key
      count is unbounded.`,
    try: `<code>tflo-wasm</code> builds with <code>wasm-pack build --target web</code>.`,
    caveats: 'Memory cap is real; bound active-key cardinality explicitly for large graphs.',
    badge: null,
  },
  {
    title: '5. no_std microcontroller',
    body: `Not supported today. <code>tflo-core</code> depends on <code>std</code>
      collections in keyed execution; lifting that requires a parallel
      <code>no_std</code>-compatible storage layer. Aspirational &mdash; the
      <a href="/docs/non-goals" class="text-primary hover:underline">non-goals</a> page
      explains why it's not a current commitment.`,
    try: null,
    caveats: 'Aspirational; tracked on the roadmap.',
    badge: null,
  },
  {
    title: '6. Batch / replay over historical data',
    body: `Run the same temporal-graph code over a bounded historical dataset. The Iterator
      path supports this natively &mdash; feed any
      <code>impl Iterator&lt;Item = Record&gt;</code> into <code>.tflo(...)</code>. Format:
      Parquet via <code>tflo-arrow</code> (<code>parquet</code> feature). Schema safety:
      stamp <code>schema_fingerprint(&amp;schema)</code> into
      <code>SnapshotMetadata.topology_fingerprint</code>; the fingerprint poka-yoke refuses a
      backfill against a structurally-different schema.`,
    try: `<code>tflo-arrow</code> <code>parquet_io::{write_batches, read_batches}</code>;
      the <code>iot-portal</code> example builds a <code>RecordBatch</code> to show the
      schema-fingerprint flow.`,
    caveats: 'Same detectors, same closures, deterministic output &mdash; that is the point.',
    badge: 'next',
  },
];
---

<DocsLayout title="Deployment shapes" description="Six concrete shapes tflo covers, with caveats that matter in production.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-2">Deployment shapes</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-text-muted mb-12">
      Six concrete shapes tflo is intended to cover. Each entry names the shape, points at
      the example or crate that demonstrates it, and lists the caveats that matter in
      production.
    </p>

    {shapes.map(shape => (
      <section class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">
          {shape.title}
          {shape.badge === 'next' && <NextReleaseBadge />}
        </h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3" set:html={shape.body} />
        {shape.try && (
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-2">
            <strong class="text-white">Try it:</strong>
            <span set:html={' ' + shape.try} />
          </p>
        )}
        {shape.caveats && (
          <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-white">Caveats:</strong>
            <span set:html={' ' + shape.caveats} />
          </p>
        )}
      </section>
    ))}

    <section class="mt-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Picking a shape</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-border">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-border bg-bg-card">
              <th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold text-white">Question</th>
              <th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold text-white">Shape</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-text-muted">
            <tr class="border-b border-border"><td class="p-4">Single Rust process, no external deps?</td><td class="p-4"><strong class="text-white">1. Embedded</strong></td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border"><td class="p-4">Linux / ARM gateway with sensor protocols?</td><td class="p-4"><strong class="text-white">2. Edge gateway</strong></td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border"><td class="p-4">Horizontal scale + restartable durable state?</td><td class="p-4"><strong class="text-white">3. Cluster</strong></td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border"><td class="p-4">Browser / WASM-host runtime?</td><td class="p-4"><strong class="text-white">4. WASM</strong></td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border"><td class="p-4">Bare-metal MCU?</td><td class="p-4"><strong class="text-white">5. no_std</strong> (aspirational)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="p-4">Backfill or simulation over recorded data?</td><td class="p-4"><strong class="text-white">6. Batch / replay</strong></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-text-muted mt-4">
        Shapes 1, 2, and 6 are production-ready today. Shape 3 ships the contracts +
        <code>KafkaShardRouter</code>; the real <code>rdkafka</code> backend is feature-gated
        and exercises a redpanda-in-docker integration when opted in. Shape 4 builds &mdash;
        the memory caveat is real. Shape 5 is roadmap.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-16 p-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-card">
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        <strong class="text-white">Canonical source:</strong>
        <a href="https://github.com/matt-cochran/tflo/blob/main/docs/deployment-shapes.md" class="text-primary hover:underline">docs/deployment-shapes.md</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted mt-3">
        <strong class="text-white">Related:</strong>
        <a href="/docs/contracts" class="text-primary hover:underline">Contracts</a>
        &middot;
        <a href="/docs/reference-deployment" class="text-primary hover:underline">Reference deployment</a>
        &middot;
        <a href="/docs/non-goals" class="text-primary hover:underline">Non-goals</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
